<!-- FLASH MODAL -->
<div id="flash_modal" class="modal fade">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
    
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h3 class="modal-title">Flash Cards</h3>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <h5>&rarr; = NEXT<br/>
        &larr; = PREV<br/>
        &uarr; = Save for Review</h5><br/>
        <b>The 'Start' button will change. </b><br/>
        <b>'Clear'</b> appears when you're at the first card in the deck in case you just need to clear the screen.<br/>
        <b>'Restart'</b> appers after you've started proceeding through the deck.<br/>
        <b>'Review'</b> and the number of items selected for review appears as soon as there are any.<br/>
        <b>'Restart Set'</b> appears at the first card in the review deck. Clicking this will remove the review deck.<br/>
        <b>'Restart Review'</b> appears after you've started proceeding through the review deck.<br/>
        <b>'Review'</b> and the number of items selected for review will appear again if you select items for further review from the review deck.<br/><br/>
        <ul>
          <li>Pro Tip 1: Some decks are sorted into pairs. Sort them alphabetically by 
          unchecking "Shuffle" when the deck is selected.</li>
          <li>Pro Tip 2: Some decks are large. Cherry pick a review deck before your
          students see them. You could even have multiple tabs set up.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- DIAGRAMS MODAL -->
<div id="diagrams_modal" class="modal fade">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
    
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h3 class="modal-title">Diagrams</h3>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        This is simply a set of images take from the A-GO brain box. 
        The cards are too small for more than one person to see at a time so
        this is a way to let the whole class see what you're talking about.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- MATCH MODAL -->
<div id="match_modal" class="modal fade">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
    
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h3 class="modal-title">Match</h3>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Share this screen via any video conferencing software.</li>
          <li>Students must choose two cards by telling the teacher what's on the back.</li>
          <li>The teacher flips them.</li>
          <li>If they match, leave them face up and continue with another student.</li>
          <li>Everyone wins!</li>
        </ul>
        <br/>
        Students can study numbers by calling out the colors on the backs of the number cards.
        Then colored numbers appear on the backs of the animal cards.
        Once they've learned the animals, they can study letters by calling out 
        the two animals that start with each letter.
        Other letters are covered with simple objects.
        They can then study shapes by calling out more colors.
        Colored shapes will become the backs of the next sets.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>



<!-- WORDLE MODAL -->
<div id="wordle_modal" class="modal fade">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
    
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h3 class="modal-title">Wordle for Spelling</h3>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>You know the word. Do you know how to spell it?</p>
        <span class="btn btn-warning">Yellow</span> = the letter is somewhere in the word.<br>
        <span class="btn btn-primary">Blue</span> = the letter is in the correct place in the word.<br>
        <span class="btn btn-secondary">Gray</span> = the letter is <em>not</em> in the word.
        <br/>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

